1. d4 {t} d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 g6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Be2 O-O 7. O-O b6 {Possible solid move. Black wants to develop the bishop on b7 or a6, and also there will be no issues with the b7 pawn.} 8. a4 $1 {[%csl Ba4] Engine's top move, but it's only White's 4th most popular one.} (8. b3 {t Tough to criticize this move, White wants to be solid.} Ne4 $5 {[%csl Yb3,Rc3][%cal Ge4c3,Yb2b3] Engine likes this move, highlighting the fact that b3 leaves the knight hanging.} 9. Bb2 (9. Nxe4 {t always important to check it, but here Black will be in time.} dxe4 10. Nd2 c5 $1 $132) 9... Nxc3 10. Bxc3 e6 $5 {[%csl Bc8] For the moment we can keep flexible Bc8: maybe it will go to a6, maybe to b7.} (10... Bb7 $132 {With a solid position.}) 11. Rc1 (11. b4 {s} Ba6 12. Qb3 Nd7 13. Rfc1 Qe7 $11 {[%cal Gf8c8] at some point we will take on c4, and it's a normal equal position.}) 11... Bb7 12. cxd5 exd5 13. b4 {Wang-Bu, 2010.} Nd7 14. a4 Qe7 $132 {[%cal Gd7f6,Gf6e4] Nf6-Ne4 next, with a normal game.}) (8. b4 {t} dxc4 9. Bxc4 b5 10. Bb3 a5 11. bxa5 Qxa5 12. Bd2 b4 13. Na4 Ne4 14. Qc2 (14. Rc1 {t} Ba6 15. Re1 Bb5 $11) 14... Bf5 15. Qc4 Qa6 16. Qxa6 Nxa6 $11 {[%cal Gc6c5]}) (8. Bd2 {t} Bb7 9. Rc1 e6 10. b4 dxc4 11. Bxc4 Nbd7 $11 {[%cal Gc6c5] c5 next. Bindrich-Van Foreest, 2018.}) 8... Ne4 $5 {could be an interesting new possibility, and it's my main recommendation if you want to play 7...b6.} (8... a5 $6 {[%csl Ra5] Mamedyarov wanted to stop a5, but Carlsen punished him in the right way.} 9. cxd5 $1 cxd5 10. b3 {[%csl Gb5][%cal Gc1a3] Ba3 next, and then White can also use the b5 square for his pieces.} Ne4 11. Nxe4 dxe4 12. Nd2 Bb7 13. Ba3 f5 14. Rc1 Kh8 15. Nc4 Nd7 16. d5 $16 {1-0 Carlsen,M (2863) -Mamedyarov,S (2756) Gashimov Memorial 2nd Shamkir 2015 (2)}) (8... Ba6 9. b3 $1 {[%csl Gb3] was the most principled try, to simply defend the center.} Ne4 10. Bb2 $14 {White gets something.}) 9. a5 {Critical.} (9. Nxe4 {t} dxe4 10. Nd2 c5 $1 11. dxc5 Na6 $5 12. cxb6 Qxb6 13. Nxe4 Rd8 $44 {[%csl Ba6,Bb6,Bd8][%cal Ga6b4,Gc8f5] Black has full compensation, according to the engine.}) (9. Qb3 {t popular but harmless:} dxc4 10. Bxc4 (10. Qxc4 {t allows easy equality:} Ba6 11. Qa2 Bxe2 12. Nxe2 c5 $11) 10... Nd6 11. Be2 c5 12. dxc5 bxc5 $132 {[%csl Rb3,Rb4][%cal Gc8e6,Gb8c6] Qb3 is misplaced.}) 9... Nxc3 $1 (9... Ba6 $2 10. Nxe4 dxe4 11. Ng5 $16 {Bu - Van Wely, 2018 Olympiad.}) 10. bxc3 Ba6 {Only three games here.} 11. h4 $5 $146 {Engine's move.} (11. Nd2 {t Huzman-Li, 2020.} dxc4 12. Nxc4 c5 {[%cal Gb8d7]} 13. axb6 axb6 14. Bf3 Ra7 $11 {[%cal Ga7c7] Rc7 next.}) (11. Re1 {t} Nd7 12. cxd5 Bxe2 13. Qxe2 cxd5 14. c4 dxc4 15. Qxc4 e5 $11 {½-½ Woodard,D (2418) -Miettinen,K (2429) USCC-ch21 email ICCF email 2018}) (11. Qb3 {t} Qc7 12. axb6 axb6 13. Ba3 c5 $15 {Black was even preferable in Bu-Bai, 2024.}) 11... bxa5 {[%csl Ba5] Principled.} (11... Nd7 12. axb6 axb6 13. Rxa6 $1 Rxa6 14. cxd5 $36 {Could be interesting for White.}) 12. Qa4 (12. h5 Nd7 13. hxg6 hxg6 14. Ng5 Nf6 $132 {Complicated new position, 0.00 by the engine.}) 12... Nd7 13. Qxa5 Bxc4 14. Bxc4 dxc4 {[%cal Gc6c5] Black is ready for c5.} 15. Qa4 c5 16. Qxc4 Qc7 $11 {[%cal Gf8c8] Rfc8 next and it's equal.} *

